c JNdkSc"><div class="JNdkSc-SmKAyb"><div class="" jscontroller="sGwD4d" jsaction="zXBUYb:zTPCnb;zQF9Uc:Qxe3nd;" jsname="F57UId"><div class="oKdM2c Kzv0Me"><div id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_51" class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-uQSCkd jXK9ad D2fZ2 OjCsFc wHaque GNzUNc"><div class="jXK9ad-SmKAyb"><div class="tyJCtd mGzaTb baZpAe"><div id="h.vtwbjvekhsbc" class="GV3q8e aP9Z7e"></div><h3 id="h.vtwbjvekhsbc" dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q OmQG5e" tabindex="-1"><div jscontroller="Ae65rd" jsaction="touchstart:UrsOsc; click:KjsqPd; focusout:QZoaZ; mouseover:y0pDld; mouseout:dq0hvd;fv1Rjc:jbFSOd;CrfLRd:SzACGe;" class="CjVfdc"><div class="PPhIP rviiZ" jsname="haAclf"><div role="presentation" class="U26fgb mUbCce fKz7Od LRAOtb Znu9nd M9Bg4d" jscontroller="mxS5xe" jsaction="click:cOuCgd; mousedown:UX7yZ; mouseup:lbsD7e; mouseenter:tfO1Yc; mouseleave:JywGue; focus:AHmuwe; blur:O22p3e; contextmenu:mg9Pef;" jsshadow="" aria-describedby="h.vtwbjvekhsbc" aria-label="Copy heading link" aria-disabled="false" data-tooltip="Copy heading link" aria-hidden="true" data-tooltip-position="top" data-tooltip-vertical-offset="12" data-tooltip-horizontal-offset="0"><a class="FKF6mc TpQm9d" href="#h.vtwbjvekhsbc" aria-label="Copy heading link" jsname="hiK3ld" role="button" aria-describedby="h.vtwbjvekhsbc"><div class="VTBa7b MbhUzd" jsname="ksKsZd"></div><span jsslot="" class="xjKiLb"><span class="Ce1Y1c" style="top: -11px"><svg class="OUGEr QdAdhf" width="22px" height="22px" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" focusable="false"><path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none"></path><path d="M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76 0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71 0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71 0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76 0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z"></path></svg></span></span></a></div></div><span style="font-family: 'Lato';"><strong>Prepping and Optimizing the Artwork for Comp</strong></span></div></h3><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Always keep the original approved art files intact.  Do not modify those.  Duplicate and save a new version when you make optimization edits. </span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">There is almost never an occasion where you should import approved designs directly into AE without doing some prep work first. </span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q"><br></p><div id="h.tfroe3tbxzcb" class="GV3q8e aP9Z7e"></div><h3 id="h.tfroe3tbxzcb" dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q OmQG5e" tabindex="-1"><div jscontroller="Ae65rd" jsaction="touchstart:UrsOsc; click:KjsqPd; focusout:QZoaZ; mouseover:y0pDld; mouseout:dq0hvd;fv1Rjc:jbFSOd;CrfLRd:SzACGe;" class="CjVfdc"><div class="PPhIP rviiZ" jsname="haAclf"><div role="presentation" class="U26fgb mUbCce fKz7Od LRAOtb Znu9nd M9Bg4d" jscontroller="mxS5xe" jsaction="click:cOuCgd; mousedown:UX7yZ; mouseup:lbsD7e; mouseenter:tfO1Yc; mouseleave:JywGue; focus:AHmuwe; blur:O22p3e; contextmenu:mg9Pef;" jsshadow="" aria-describedby="h.tfroe3tbxzcb" aria-label="Copy heading link" aria-disabled="false" data-tooltip="Copy heading link" aria-hidden="true" data-tooltip-position="top" data-tooltip-vertical-offset="12" data-tooltip-horizontal-offset="0"><a class="FKF6mc TpQm9d" href="#h.tfroe3tbxzcb" aria-label="Copy heading link" jsname="hiK3ld" role="button" aria-describedby="h.tfroe3tbxzcb"><div class="VTBa7b MbhUzd" jsname="ksKsZd"></div><span jsslot="" class="xjKiLb"><span class="Ce1Y1c" style="top: -11px"><svg class="OUGEr QdAdhf" width="22px" height="22px" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" focusable="false"><path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none"></path><path d="M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76 0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71 0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71 0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76 0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z"></path></svg></span></span></a></div></div>PSD File Prep Tips:</div></h3><ol class="n8H08c BKnRcf" style="list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0; padding: 0;"><li dir="ltr" class="TYR86d wXCUfe zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt;"><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 0; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Reduce file size by merging and rescaling PSD art for AE.</span></p></li></ol><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">If you aren’t zooming in very tight or doing a long pan, there’s seldom a reason to use a PSD that is 6k+ resolution. Reduce PSD size to be 4K square (3840 x 3840). This can potentially reduce render times by HALF!</span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q"><br></p><ol class="n8H08c BKnRcf" style="list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0; padding: 0;" start="2"><li dir="ltr" class="TYR86d wXCUfe zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt;"><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 0; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Move and rename PSDs to appropriate ae assets folder:</span></p></li></ol><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">01_ae -&gt; 02_ae_assets -&gt; 02_psd-raster</span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Prep files and move to psd or ai folders accordingly within ae assets. </span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section><section id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_65" class="yaqOZd" style=""><div class="IFuOkc"></div><div class="mYVXT"><div class="LS81yb VICjCf" tabindex="-1"><div class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-OiUrBf purZT-AhqUyc-II5mzb pSzOP-AhqUyc-qWD73c JNdkSc"><div class="JNdkSc-SmKAyb"><div class="" jscontroller="sGwD4d" jsaction="zXBUYb:zTPCnb;zQF9Uc:Qxe3nd;" jsname="F57UId"><div class="oKdM2c Kzv0Me"><div id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_62" class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-OiUrBf jXK9ad D2fZ2 OjCsFc wHaque GNzUNc"><div class="jXK9ad-SmKAyb"><div class="tyJCtd mGzaTb baZpAe"><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">3. Rename files so they are consistent in shot naming.  </span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Oftentimes there are several designers working on one project and their naming conventions/shot numbers are not up to date. This can make tracking down specific PSDs difficult. Sample naming convention here.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-II5mzb purZT-AhqUyc-II5mzb pSzOP-AhqUyc-II5mzb JNdkSc"><div class="JNdkSc-SmKAyb"><div class="" jscontroller="sGwD4d" jsaction="zXBUYb:zTPCnb;zQF9Uc:Qxe3nd;" jsname="F57UId"><div class="oKdM2c Kzv0Me"><div id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_55" class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-II5mzb pSzOP-AhqUyc-II5mzb jXK9ad D2fZ2 OjCsFc wHaque"><div class="jXK9ad-SmKAyb"><div class="tyJCtd baZpAe"><div class="t3iYD"><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/X_JoTcnV-u0EPVwsI-7Juh2LstVa_e5BWBJb6ZsM4IEjHivaEvjKF_vMzr1j8buVkUOoYn8Q9B0j_JwzCujIc79Md8WcrqDFlGu9sL-Zx52jzTdyNCloAlwK6FYdbYwwmQ=w1280" class="CENy8b" role="img"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section><section id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_69" class="yaqOZd" style=""><div class="IFuOkc"></div><div class="mYVXT"><div class="LS81yb VICjCf" tabindex="-1"><div class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-uQSCkd purZT-AhqUyc-II5mzb pSzOP-AhqUyc-qWD73c JNdkSc"><div class="JNdkSc-SmKAyb"><div class="" jscontroller="sGwD4d" jsaction="zXBUYb:zTPCnb;zQF9Uc:Qxe3nd;" jsname="F57UId"><div class="oKdM2c Kzv0Me"><div id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_66" class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-uQSCkd jXK9ad D2fZ2 OjCsFc wHaque GNzUNc"><div class="jXK9ad-SmKAyb"><div class="tyJCtd mGzaTb baZpAe"><div id="h.8pem8yfwdkvw" class="GV3q8e aP9Z7e"></div><h3 id="h.8pem8yfwdkvw" dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q OmQG5e" tabindex="-1"><div jscontroller="Ae65rd" jsaction="touchstart:UrsOsc; click:KjsqPd; focusout:QZoaZ; mouseover:y0pDld; mouseout:dq0hvd;fv1Rjc:jbFSOd;CrfLRd:SzACGe;" class="CjVfdc"><div class="PPhIP rviiZ" jsname="haAclf"><div role="presentation" class="U26fgb mUbCce fKz7Od LRAOtb Znu9nd M9Bg4d" jscontroller="mxS5xe" jsaction="click:cOuCgd; mousedown:UX7yZ; mouseup:lbsD7e; mouseenter:tfO1Yc; mouseleave:JywGue; focus:AHmuwe; blur:O22p3e; contextmenu:mg9Pef;" jsshadow="" aria-describedby="h.8pem8yfwdkvw" aria-label="Copy heading link" aria-disabled="false" data-tooltip="Copy heading link" aria-hidden="true" data-tooltip-position="top" data-tooltip-vertical-offset="12" data-tooltip-horizontal-offset="0"><a class="FKF6mc TpQm9d" href="#h.8pem8yfwdkvw" aria-label="Copy heading link" jsname="hiK3ld" role="button" aria-describedby="h.8pem8yfwdkvw"><div class="VTBa7b MbhUzd" jsname="ksKsZd"></div><span jsslot="" class="xjKiLb"><span class="Ce1Y1c" style="top: -11px"><svg class="OUGEr QdAdhf" width="22px" height="22px" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" focusable="false"><path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none"></path><path d="M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76 0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71 0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71 0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76 0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z"></path></svg></span></span></a></div></div>Ai File Prep Tips:</div></h3><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q"><br></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="background-color: transparent; border-bottom: none; border-left: none; border-right: none; border-top: none; line-height: 1.656; margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 36pt; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; padding-top: 0; text-align: left; text-indent: 0;"><span style="color: #000000; font-family: 'Lato'; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>Texture File</strong></span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="background-color: transparent; border-bottom: none; border-left: none; border-right: none; border-top: none; line-height: 1.656; margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 36pt; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; padding-top: 0; text-align: left; text-indent: 0;"><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Designers should also provide you with a texture PSD along with any bespoke brushes they used for Ai or PS in case you need to make a very specific texture element for matting.   If this has not been provided, please ask your Producer if that can be acquired.</span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="background-color: transparent; border-bottom: none; border-left: none; border-right: none; border-top: none; line-height: 1.656; margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 36pt; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; padding-top: 0; text-align: left; text-indent: 0;"><br></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="background-color: transparent; border-bottom: none; border-left: none; border-right: none; border-top: none; line-height: 1.656; margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 36pt; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; padding-top: 0; text-align: left; text-indent: 0;"><span style="color: #000000; font-family: 'Lato'; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>Workflow</strong></span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="background-color: transparent; border-bottom: none; border-left: none; border-right: none; border-top: none; line-height: 1.656; margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 36pt; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; padding-top: 0; text-align: left; text-indent: 0;"><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">If the designer created the files in Ai and added textures in PS, you should recreate the look of the approved art in AE using the Ai layers (or shape layers if you have converted them) and the texture file you receive from the designers. </span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="background-color: transparent; border-bottom: none; border-left: none; border-right: none; border-top: none; line-height: 1.656; margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 36pt; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; padding-top: 0; text-align: left; text-indent: 0;"><br></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="background-color: transparent; border-bottom: none; border-left: none; border-right: none; border-top: none; line-height: 1.656; margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 36pt; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; padding-top: 0; text-align: left; text-indent: 0;"><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Use the Ai/shape layers as an alpha matte for your PS textures. This will give you the greatest flexibility to edit art on the fly. You can also create the textures using a bright red brush in PS, then add a “Fill” effect in AE to change the texture color as needed. </span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="background-color: transparent; border-bottom: none; border-left: none; border-right: none; border-top: none; line-height: 1.656; margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 36pt; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; padding-top: 0; text-align: left; text-indent: 0;"><br></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="background-color: transparent; border-bottom: none; border-left: none; border-right: none; border-top: none; line-height: 1.656; margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 36pt; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; padding-top: 0; text-align: left; text-indent: 0;"><span style="color: #000000; font-family: 'Lato'; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>Mimic PS brush edges</strong></span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="background-color: transparent; border-bottom: none; border-left: none; border-right: none; border-top: none; line-height: 1.656; margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 36pt; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; padding-top: 0; text-align: left; text-indent: 0;"><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">If your art has a rough paper tooth texture edge and you’re using vector art, use the ROUGHEN EDGES plugin and adjust settings as needed. This can do the trick to simulate almost any PS brush you need to match the look of. </span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section><section id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_73" class="yaqOZd" style=""><div class="IFuOkc"></div><div class="mYVXT"><div class="LS81yb VICjCf" tabindex="-1"><div class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-uQSCkd purZT-AhqUyc-II5mzb pSzOP-AhqUyc-qWD73c JNdkSc"><div class="JNdkSc-SmKAyb"><div class="" jscontroller="sGwD4d" jsaction="zXBUYb:zTPCnb;zQF9Uc:Qxe3nd;" jsname="F57UId"><div class="oKdM2c Kzv0Me"><div id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_70" class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-uQSCkd jXK9ad D2fZ2 OjCsFc wHaque GNzUNc"><div class="jXK9ad-SmKAyb"><div class="tyJCtd mGzaTb baZpAe"><div id="h.tc0bbajg7e3u" class="GV3q8e aP9Z7e"></div><h3 id="h.tc0bbajg7e3u" dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q OmQG5e" tabindex="-1"><div jscontroller="Ae65rd" jsaction="touchstart:UrsOsc; click:KjsqPd; focusout:QZoaZ; mouseover:y0pDld; mouseout:dq0hvd;fv1Rjc:jbFSOd;CrfLRd:SzACGe;" class="CjVfdc"><div class="PPhIP rviiZ" jsname="haAclf"><div role="presentation" class="U26fgb mUbCce fKz7Od LRAOtb Znu9nd M9Bg4d" jscontroller="mxS5xe" jsaction="click:cOuCgd; mousedown:UX7yZ; mouseup:lbsD7e; mouseenter:tfO1Yc; mouseleave:JywGue; focus:AHmuwe; blur:O22p3e; contextmenu:mg9Pef;" jsshadow="" aria-describedby="h.tc0bbajg7e3u" aria-label="Copy heading link" aria-disabled="false" data-tooltip="Copy heading link" aria-hidden="true" data-tooltip-position="top" data-tooltip-vertical-offset="12" data-tooltip-horizontal-offset="0"><a class="FKF6mc TpQm9d" href="#h.tc0bbajg7e3u" aria-label="Copy heading link" jsname="hiK3ld" role="button" aria-describedby="h.tc0bbajg7e3u"><div class="VTBa7b MbhUzd" jsname="ksKsZd"></div><span jsslot="" class="xjKiLb"><span class="Ce1Y1c" style="top: -11px"><svg class="OUGEr QdAdhf" width="22px" height="22px" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" focusable="false"><path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none"></path><path d="M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76 0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71 0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71 0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76 0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z"></path></svg></span></span></a></div></div><span style="font-family: 'Lato';"><strong>Cutdowns/Social Crops</strong></span></div></h3><ol class="n8H08c BKnRcf" style="list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0; padding: 0;"><li dir="ltr" class="TYR86d wXCUfe zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt;"><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 0; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Always build 9x16 as your hero social crop.</span></p></li></ol><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">If done correctly, 1x1 and 4x5s should be able to be cut from this video in Premiere.</span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><br></p><ol class="n8H08c BKnRcf" style="list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0; padding: 0;" start="2"><li dir="ltr" class="TYR86d wXCUfe zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt;"><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 0; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">You can and should talk to 2D to ask for extended size animations. </span></p></li></ol><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">You may realize that in your vertical version the character isn’t tall enough to fill frame. Simply show 2D a reference image of your comp and they can extend their animation for you.</span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><br></p><ol class="n8H08c BKnRcf" style="list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0; padding: 0;" start="3"><li dir="ltr" class="TYR86d wXCUfe zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt;"><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 0; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">End Cards</span></p></li></ol><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">When possible, build end cards to be the exact size of your exports.</span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Example: You have a 1080x1920 export, your end card should be 1080x1920. We frequently need to swap end cards so this will save time down the line.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section><section id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_77" class="yaqOZd" style=""><div class="IFuOkc"></div><div class="mYVXT"><div class="LS81yb VICjCf" tabindex="-1"><div class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-wNfPc purZT-AhqUyc-II5mzb pSzOP-AhqUyc-qWD73c JNdkSc"><div class="JNdkSc-SmKAyb"><div class="" jscontroller="sGwD4d" jsaction="zXBUYb:zTPCnb;zQF9Uc:Qxe3nd;" jsname="F57UId"><div class="oKdM2c Kzv0Me"><div id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_74" class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-wNfPc pSzOP-AhqUyc-qWD73c jXK9ad D2fZ2 OjCsFc wHaque GNzUNc"><div class="jXK9ad-SmKAyb"><div class="tyJCtd mGzaTb baZpAe"><div id="h.lppmxr4i5zjm" class="GV3q8e aP9Z7e"></div><h3 id="h.lppmxr4i5zjm" dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q OmQG5e" tabindex="-1"><div jscontroller="Ae65rd" jsaction="touchstart:UrsOsc; click:KjsqPd; focusout:QZoaZ; mouseover:y0pDld; mouseout:dq0hvd;fv1Rjc:jbFSOd;CrfLRd:SzACGe;" class="CjVfdc"><div class="PPhIP rviiZ" jsname="haAclf"><div role="presentation" class="U26fgb mUbCce fKz7Od LRAOtb Znu9nd M9Bg4d" jscontroller="mxS5xe" jsaction="click:cOuCgd; mousedown:UX7yZ; mouseup:lbsD7e; mouseenter:tfO1Yc; mouseleave:JywGue; focus:AHmuwe; blur:O22p3e; contextmenu:mg9Pef;" jsshadow="" aria-describedby="h.lppmxr4i5zjm" aria-label="Copy heading link" aria-disabled="false" data-tooltip="Copy heading link" aria-hidden="true" data-tooltip-position="top" data-tooltip-vertical-offset="12" data-tooltip-horizontal-offset="0"><a class="FKF6mc TpQm9d" href="#h.lppmxr4i5zjm" aria-label="Copy heading link" jsname="hiK3ld" role="button" aria-describedby="h.lppmxr4i5zjm"><div class="VTBa7b MbhUzd" jsname="ksKsZd"></div><span jsslot="" class="xjKiLb"><span class="Ce1Y1c" style="top: -11px"><svg class="OUGEr QdAdhf" width="22px" height="22px" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" focusable="false"><path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none"></path><path d="M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76 0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71 0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71 0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76 0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z"></path></svg></span></span></a></div></div><span style="font-family: 'Lato';"><strong>Workflow Best Practices + Watch Outs</strong></span></div></h3><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-family: 'Lato'; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>Use a One-Node Camera (don’t using multiple camera nulls)</strong></span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Under “Type” settings, select 1 node camera. This doesn’t use the “point of interest” and makes the camera function as if it was a standard 3d layer. </span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><br></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">If you want to look at something specific, simply adjust the rotation/position values of the camera. </span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><br></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Making edits to this type of camera is significantly easier than a Two-Node cam.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-OwsYgb purZT-AhqUyc-II5mzb pSzOP-AhqUyc-qWD73c JNdkSc"><div class="JNdkSc-SmKAyb"><div class="" jscontroller="sGwD4d" jsaction="zXBUYb:zTPCnb;zQF9Uc:Qxe3nd;" jsname="F57UId"><div class="oKdM2c Kzv0Me"><div id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_78" class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-OwsYgb jXK9ad D2fZ2 OjCsFc wHaque"><div class="jXK9ad-SmKAyb"><div class="tyJCtd baZpAe"><div class="t3iYD"><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/N-j4wHLcFDKlBjuJIraPFcTb8h4_HssHbT7BT5HKMyfg6UbVryPqURvka0x44YJ-4_HuVwjJWXkpnhMPI9Ln-mpkFuy6atAqLZDA-S4krcCeUKnrggoRc-wk7eqM-eYCfA=w1280" class="CENy8b" role="img"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section><section id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_85" class="yaqOZd" style=""><div class="IFuOkc"></div><div class="mYVXT"><div class="LS81yb VICjCf" tabindex="-1"><div class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-uQSCkd purZT-AhqUyc-II5mzb pSzOP-AhqUyc-qWD73c JNdkSc"><div class="JNdkSc-SmKAyb"><div class="" jscontroller="sGwD4d" jsaction="zXBUYb:zTPCnb;zQF9Uc:Qxe3nd;" jsname="F57UId"><div class="oKdM2c Kzv0Me"><div id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_82" class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-uQSCkd jXK9ad D2fZ2 OjCsFc wHaque GNzUNc"><div class="jXK9ad-SmKAyb"><div class="tyJCtd mGzaTb baZpAe"><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-family: 'Lato'; font-size: 12pt; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>Things to Avoid</strong></span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 30pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-family: 'Lato'; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>Extreme Z Space Values</strong></span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 30pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Create Z depth ideally under 10,0000 px. Extreme depth can slow render times and make it difficult to locate layers in top view. If you need something to look deeper, try adjusting your camera settings. I.E. use a 200mm camera instead of 50mm.</span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 30pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-family: 'Lato'; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>DOF on Cameras</strong></span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 30pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">Slow. Very slow. </span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 30pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-family: 'Lato'; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>Motion Blur</strong></span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 30pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">You can use motion blur if needed, but it will slow your renders for sure. Perhaps try a directional gaussian blur on an adjustment layer to fake motion blur when you need it if it’s rendering slowly.</span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 30pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-family: 'Lato'; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>Large Particle Generators</strong></span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 30pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">They should not exceed 1080x1920 or 1920x1080. If you are using Particular, create a solid that is your comp size and apply the effect to that. Change your emitter width instead of widening the layer size. Your particles will still emit as though you had a much wider layer. This can save HOURS of rendering.</span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><br></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section><section id="h.56e95cbdacedae36_50" class="yaqOZd" style=""><div class="IFuOkc"></div><div class="mYVXT"><div class="LS81yb VICjCf" tabindex="-1"><div class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-uQSCkd purZT-AhqUyc-II5mzb pSzOP-AhqUyc-qWD73c JNdkSc"><div class="JNdkSc-SmKAyb"><div class="" jscontroller="sGwD4d" jsaction="zXBUYb:zTPCnb;zQF9Uc:Qxe3nd;" jsname="F57UId"><div class="oKdM2c Kzv0Me"><div id="h.56e95cbdacedae36_47" class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-uQSCkd jXK9ad D2fZ2 OjCsFc wHaque GNzUNc"><div class="jXK9ad-SmKAyb"><div class="tyJCtd mGzaTb baZpAe"><div id="h.etlqgqi3rmzm" class="GV3q8e aP9Z7e"></div><h3 id="h.etlqgqi3rmzm" dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q OmQG5e" tabindex="-1"><div jscontroller="Ae65rd" jsaction="touchstart:UrsOsc; click:KjsqPd; focusout:QZoaZ; mouseover:y0pDld; mouseout:dq0hvd;fv1Rjc:jbFSOd;CrfLRd:SzACGe;" class="CjVfdc"><div class="PPhIP rviiZ" jsname="haAclf"><div role="presentation" class="U26fgb mUbCce fKz7Od LRAOtb Znu9nd M9Bg4d" jscontroller="mxS5xe" jsaction="click:cOuCgd; mousedown:UX7yZ; mouseup:lbsD7e; mouseenter:tfO1Yc; mouseleave:JywGue; focus:AHmuwe; blur:O22p3e; contextmenu:mg9Pef;" jsshadow="" aria-describedby="h.etlqgqi3rmzm" aria-label="Copy heading link" aria-disabled="false" data-tooltip="Copy heading link" aria-hidden="true" data-tooltip-position="top" data-tooltip-vertical-offset="12" data-tooltip-horizontal-offset="0"><a class="FKF6mc TpQm9d" href="#h.etlqgqi3rmzm" aria-label="Copy heading link" jsname="hiK3ld" role="button" aria-describedby="h.etlqgqi3rmzm"><div class="VTBa7b MbhUzd" jsname="ksKsZd"></div><span jsslot="" class="xjKiLb"><span class="Ce1Y1c" style="top: -11px"><svg class="OUGEr QdAdhf" width="22px" height="22px" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" focusable="false"><path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none"></path><path d="M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76 0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71 0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71 0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76 0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z"></path></svg></span></span></a></div></div><span style="font-family: 'Lato';"><strong>Protip for Naming Renders</strong></span></div></h3><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">You can create a custom output module so you don’t need to rename your renders every time.  Once you get this set up, you can use it across any project -  it even remembers it between AE updates.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section><section id="h.56e95cbdacedae36_58" class="yaqOZd" style=""><div class="IFuOkc"></div><div class="mYVXT"><div class="LS81yb VICjCf" tabindex="-1"><div class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-uQSCkd purZT-AhqUyc-II5mzb pSzOP-AhqUyc-qWD73c JNdkSc yYI8W "><div class="JNdkSc-SmKAyb"><div class="" jscontroller="sGwD4d" jsaction="zXBUYb:zTPCnb;zQF9Uc:Qxe3nd;" jsname="F57UId"><div class="oKdM2c Kzv0Me"><div id="h.56e95cbdacedae36_55" class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-uQSCkd jXK9ad D2fZ2 OjCsFc GNzUNc"><div class="jXK9ad-SmKAyb"><div class="tyJCtd mGzaTb baZpAe"><ol class="n8H08c BKnRcf" style="list-style-type: decimal; margin-left: 0; margin-right: 0; padding: 0;"><li dir="ltr" class="TYR86d wXCUfe zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 30pt;"><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 0; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">In your render queue, click that down arrow next to the Output To:  </span></p></li></ol></div></div></div></div><div class="oKdM2c"><div id="h.56e95cbdacedae36_51" class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-uQSCkd jXK9ad D2fZ2 wHaque"><div class="jXK9ad-SmKAyb"><div class="tyJCtd baZpAe"><div class="t3iYD"><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/qcSI7SkockS_o2fKku0QbRA0i5YKMYb0AbN9CAW8xHO_9SFwJmrpCXSE_Qtxeud6KlISdGcZy1Vt4zCFFjkEavZUxgsdERZx-eUTzbPINSoXVO6xe7N6Ug1NxDiwXZE56g=w1280" class="CENy8b" role="img"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section><section id="h.56e95cbdacedae36_63" class="yaqOZd" style=""><div class="IFuOkc"></div><div class="mYVXT"><div class="LS81yb VICjCf" tabindex="-1"><div class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-qWD73c purZT-AhqUyc-II5mzb pSzOP-AhqUyc-qWD73c JNdkSc yYI8W "><div class="JNdkSc-SmKAyb"><div class="" jscontroller="sGwD4d" jsaction="zXBUYb:zTPCnb;zQF9Uc:Qxe3nd;" jsname="F57UId"><div class="oKdM2c Kzv0Me"><div id="h.56e95cbdacedae36_60" class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-qWD73c jXK9ad D2fZ2 OjCsFc GNzUNc"><div class="jXK9ad-SmKAyb"><div class="tyJCtd mGzaTb baZpAe"><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">2. </span><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; font-style: normal; text-decoration: normal; vertical-align: baseline;">Select </span><span style="color: #000000; font-family: 'Lato'; font-size: 12pt; font-style: normal; text-decoration: normal; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>“Custom…” </strong></span><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; font-style: normal; text-decoration: normal; vertical-align: baseline;">It will open up this dialogue</span><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">:</span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="oKdM2c"><div id="h.56e95cbdacedae36_64" class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-qWD73c jXK9ad D2fZ2 wHaque"><div class="jXK9ad-SmKAyb"><div class="tyJCtd baZpAe"><div class="t3iYD"><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/PcjRFz6GrzQWolf76EjdY7R7ds1p-o3QKJmlfenlEuQ3t2qkBW_PpdZ63xqFBs7Q6-B0NXqA9OHQz0NWmFCFy7Q3YztDG3Tg6SMJUWPnr7EjIMlEHnrfyGSkJJOXOTicfA=w1280" class="CENy8b" role="img"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-qWD73c JNdkSc L6cTce-purZT L6cTce-pSzOP"><div class="JNdkSc-SmKAyb"><div class="" jscontroller="sGwD4d" jsaction="zXBUYb:zTPCnb;zQF9Uc:Qxe3nd;" jsname="F57UId"></div></div></div></div></div></section><section id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_3" class="yaqOZd" style=""><div class="IFuOkc"></div><div class="mYVXT"><div class="LS81yb VICjCf" tabindex="-1"><div class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-uQSCkd purZT-AhqUyc-II5mzb pSzOP-AhqUyc-qWD73c JNdkSc"><div class="JNdkSc-SmKAyb"><div class="" jscontroller="sGwD4d" jsaction="zXBUYb:zTPCnb;zQF9Uc:Qxe3nd;" jsname="F57UId"><div class="oKdM2c Kzv0Me"><div id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_0" class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-uQSCkd jXK9ad D2fZ2 OjCsFc wHaque GNzUNc"><div class="jXK9ad-SmKAyb"><div class="tyJCtd mGzaTb baZpAe"><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="background-color: transparent; border-bottom: none; border-left: none; border-right: none; border-top: none; line-height: 1.656; margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; padding-top: 0; text-align: left; text-indent: 0;"><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">3.</span><span style="color: #000000; font-family: 'Lato'; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong> </strong></span><span style="color: #000000; font-family: 'Lato'; font-size: 12pt; font-style: normal; text-decoration: normal; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>COPY/PASTE THIS TEXT</strong></span><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; font-style: normal; text-decoration: normal; vertical-align: baseline;"> into your “Template:” text field:</span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="background-color: transparent; border-bottom: none; border-left: none; border-right: none; border-top: none; line-height: 1.656; margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; padding-top: 0; text-align: left; text-indent: 0;"><span style="color: #000000; font-family: 'Lato'; font-size: 12pt; font-style: normal; text-decoration: normal; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>[compName]_[dateYear][dateMonth][dateDay]_v01.[fileExtension]</strong></span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="background-color: transparent; border-bottom: none; border-left: none; border-right: none; border-top: none; line-height: 1.656; margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; padding-top: 0; text-align: left; text-indent: 0;"><br></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="background-color: transparent; border-bottom: none; border-left: none; border-right: none; border-top: none; line-height: 1.656; margin-bottom: 0; margin-left: 15pt; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; padding-top: 0; text-align: left; text-indent: 0;"><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">4.</span><span style="color: #000000; font-family: 'Lato'; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong> </strong></span><span style="color: #000000; font-family: 'Lato'; font-size: 12pt; font-style: normal; text-decoration: normal; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>Press the new preset button </strong></span><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; font-style: normal; text-decoration: normal; vertical-align: baseline;">(looks like a layer button). </span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">5. </span><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; font-style: normal; text-decoration: normal; vertical-align: baseline;">Name your Preset IE: </span><span style="color: #000000; font-family: 'Lato'; font-size: 12pt; font-style: normal; text-decoration: normal; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>YearMonthDay_v01, </strong></span><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">click OK</span></p><p dir="ltr" class="CDt4Ke zfr3Q" style="margin-left: 15pt; padding-left: 0; text-indent: 0;"><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; vertical-align: baseline;">6. Then select “Default” back on the main menu. Every time you add a new file to your queue, it will automatically be given this naming convention.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section><section id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_10" class="yaqOZd" style=""><div class="IFuOkc"></div><div class="mYVXT"><div class="LS81yb VICjCf" tabindex="-1"><div class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-qWD73c purZT-AhqUyc-II5mzb pSzOP-AhqUyc-qWD73c JNdkSc"><div class="JNdkSc-SmKAyb"><div class="" jscontroller="sGwD4d" jsaction="zXBUYb:zTPCnb;zQF9Uc:Qxe3nd;" jsname="F57UId"><div class="oKdM2c Kzv0Me"><div id="h.4d5e03e885f40463_28" class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-qWD73c jXK9ad D2fZ2 OjCsFc wHaque"><div class="jXK9ad-SmKAyb"><div class="tyJCtd baZpAe"><div class="t3iYD"><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/wIo9aWTYN2AJ4njSGFcfmKQcXpx8WT6fwZs-ab7UFofabNTHYybWZtanzp-80RI4uXOmpvCS255UjGNj65rNvh3lg5WKQ_o-YebrLP4UKO2Noquvz97LLZmbBMHfzuq2dA=w1280" class="CENy8b" role="img"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="hJDwNd-AhqUyc-qWD73c purZT-AhqUyc-II5mzb pSzOP-AhqUyc-qWD73c JNdkSc"><div class="JNdkSc-SmKAyb"><div class="" jscontroller="sGwD4d" jsaction="zXBUYb:zTPCnb;zQF9Uc: