3	general/cg-folder-structure	28904843cad5776a75d172d8b55962dacca14528	CG Folder Structure Overview		f	t	\N			# CG Folder Structure Overview\n![](https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/MoPAg31jbdRCQp0A42byZbY1oZ68gYR8A2dNg8x-d7rBz-NXm1lIkCzR2GvCpW0fqOQpKJQJuQsMnm4IL5v7c8xgx5G6Dxz3hFfuVCE3Hg-3Dwx4_XaTdjcu_8udL4tPog=w1280)\n### Basic Folder Structure Organization\n\nThe folder structure for each project can be tweaked at the start of a job. The leads and producer should decide on specifics of any changes to be made to suit any given project's needs. However, below is a description of the basic template for a 2d (cel) job's folder structure on the server.\n\n#### client_assets\nWhere anything from the client gets filed, organized by asset type, then dated folders within. \n\nIf the client sends a design that we have to match in Production, it will also go into the reference folder.\n\n#### dailies\nDaily, dated progress from the team, such as:\n\n- Internal animation WIPs from the team for director review.\n- \n- Internal storyboard/animatic/design WIPs from the team for director review.\n- \n- Exports from the animation team before the production gets to comp (for edit to post).  \n\n#### decks\n\nObsolete - moving to Google Slides.\n\n#### edit\nFolder for editors to share files with the rest of the production team.\n\n- **edl** - Output for conform on the floor.\n- \n- **footage** -  Where the footage for edit from a shoot is located.\n- \n- **offline** - for vfx/mixed media projects, please refer to reference -> edit_ref for the latest full edit.\n\n#### masters\nMaster files are filed by date, descriptor, or date_descriptor depending on the job.\n\n- **delivery_specs** - PDFs or e-mails describing the delivery specs for the masters.\n- \n- **hornet** - where the Hornet web masters are outputted.\n- \n- **YYMMDD** - dated folder by delivery date - spot masters organized within.\n\n#### pitch\nFolder where all materials for the pitching stage of a project are located.\n\n#### post\nLatest presentations for client organized into dated folders.\n\n#### production\n**2d** - Folder where the 2d animation team stores their work files, in shot by shot folders organized by spot. Animation files can be organized into folders based on software if more than one piece of animation software is being used for 2D production on a given shot.    \n\n**assets** - Folder for assets that are created internally that apply to various shots in the project. Assets are organized by software or context (ie: brushes, harmony, after effects, etc).\n\n**comp** - folder where compositor (AE) work files are stored, organized by spot.  Collects are also filed here.\n\n**design** - Folder where working files for designs are located, organized by asset type or shot, depending on the type of project.  Organization to be determined at the tech kick-off. Images for posting will be filed into the dailies folder by date at the root of the project folder.\n\n**renders** - organized by spot name then by shot for animator PNGs (one folder per level, _old for archiving PNGs before overwriting).  Compositor timeline renders go into edit folder within renders by date.\n\n**storyboards** - Folder for working files of storyboard artists and their exports (image sequences for animatics/shooting boards), organized by spot.  Storyboard artists who output their own timed animatics should output to dailies for director review and posting in edit.\n\n#### reference\nFolder where all approved materials are stored. They should be organized contextually and this structure can be determined at the Tech kickoff meeting.  This folder also includes the approved animatic and shot refs.\n\n#### vendor\nFolder where any production assets coming from an outside vendor - ie casting, audio, information for tracking.\n\nto_vendor is like a post folder for internal production purposes between Hornet and the outside vendor. \n\nfrom_vendor are the assets, WIPS, etc from the vendor. Each folder has 